    <note>Ren(1) Zhongshi [877] The Song Dachen nianbiao errs in writing Zhongsi for Zhongshi for 1041-43 in state council. He was a cousin or brother of Zhongzheng [875] and Zhongxing [876]. His son, Gongzhi's [3428] son-in-law was Liang(1) Shi's [1137] son, Yanshen [3565]. Gongzhi's fathers-in-law were Li(2) Zhaoshu [987], and Wang(2) Yuan(2) [8156]. Zhongshi's son or nephew, Yuanqing [3431], was Wen(2) Yanbo's [1953] son-in-law. Li(2) Bing's [8082] father-in-law, Ren(1) Li [3429], was a probable descendant. XCB, 413.11a-14a; Guangdong TZ, 15.8b; SS, 211.6a, 288.2b; Su Song, WJ, 58.13b. CBD, 1, 657-8.</note>
